docs.abstract: The cable network won more Emmys than anyone else on Sunday night, but competition is growing and its new leadership has little entertainment experience.
docs.snippet: The cable network won more Emmys than anyone else on Sunday night, but competition is growing and its new leadership has little entertainment experience.
docs.lead_paragraph: WEST HOLLYWOOD, Calif. — The champagne was flowing. HBO had just capped off another triumphant night at the Emmys, and it was time to party in the courtyard of the mammoth Pacific Design Center.

headline.main: As HBO Celebrates a Big Night, Questions About Its Future Loom
headline.print_headline: HBO Glory, But Rivals Are Gaining

byline.original: By John Koblin and Nicole Sperling

docs.abstract: The artists behind the trippy new animated series, from the creator of “BoJack Horseman,” discuss how it all came together.
docs.snippet: The artists behind the trippy new animated series, from the creator of “BoJack Horseman,” discuss how it all came together.
docs.lead_paragraph: Raphael Bob-Waksberg and Kate Purdy work together on the Emmy-nominated Hollywood satire “BoJack Horseman.” But their latest animated series delivers a narrative that’s even more surreal than the tribulations of a self-loathing talking horse.

headline.main: How ‘Undone’ Takes Viewers Through the Looking Glass
headline.print_headline: Animated Odyssey Stretches Limits of Reality

docs.abstract: With the U.S. unemployment rate near a 50-year low, openings at the company keep piling up as it tries to grow in different directions.
docs.snippet: With the U.S. unemployment rate near a 50-year low, openings at the company keep piling up as it tries to grow in different directions.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Engineers in the Bay Area. Advertising managers in Chicago. Freight specialists in Arizona. The job listings keep piling up at Amazon, a company that is growing in many directions amid one of the tightest labor markets in memory.

headline.main: Amazon Has 30,000 Open Jobs. Yes, You Read That Right.

docs.abstract: The company addresses a longtime complaint of audiophiles by offering improved audio for 50 million songs. It will cost $15 a month, $13 for members.
docs.snippet: The company addresses a longtime complaint of audiophiles by offering improved audio for 50 million songs. It will cost $15 a month, $13 for members.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon is hoping high-fidelity digital audio will appeal to all kinds of music fans, not just music snobs.

headline.main: Amazon Offers Millions of Songs in High-Quality Audio. Even Neil Young Approves.
headline.print_headline: Amazon Offers Better Audio To Subscribers, Winning a Fan

docs.abstract: Margrethe Vestager, whose billion-dollar fines have made her loathed by Silicon Valley, has won new powers that give her unrivaled regulatory reach. President Trump says she “hates the United States.”
docs.snippet: Margrethe Vestager, whose billion-dollar fines have made her loathed by Silicon Valley, has won new powers that give her unrivaled regulatory reach. President Trump says she “hates the United States.”
docs.lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — For five years, Margrethe Vestager was the scourge of Silicon Valley, levying billions of dollars in fines and initiating investigations against Google, Apple and Facebook for violating antitrust laws and harming consumers.

headline.main: E.U.’s New Digital Czar: ‘Most Powerful Regulator of Big Tech on the Planet’
headline.print_headline: E.U.’s New Digital Czar Expands Her Portfolio

docs.abstract: New devices were introduced on Wednesday to get the digital assistant in your earbuds, in your eyeglasses and in your bathroom.
docs.snippet: New devices were introduced on Wednesday to get the digital assistant in your earbuds, in your eyeglasses and in your bathroom.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Alexa has already made herself at home in kitchens and living rooms. Now Amazon is trying to get her in your ears. And on your face. And in your bathroom.

headline.main: Amazon Wants Alexa to Move (With You) Far Beyond the Living Room
headline.print_headline: Amazon Aims To Put Alexa Everywhere That You Go

docs.abstract: The live-streaming platform, owned by Amazon, has more viewers than many cable channels. But a new ad campaign aims to show it’s good for more than video games.
docs.snippet: The live-streaming platform, owned by Amazon, has more viewers than many cable channels. But a new ad campaign aims to show it’s good for more than video games.
docs.lead_paragraph: Without video games, Twitch would not be what it is now: a live-streaming platform with millions of devoted viewers and broadcasters, some of them with tattoos of the company’s logo. But the company, which Amazon bought five years ago for more than $1 billion, has ambitions beyond serving fans of Fortnite and World of Warcraft.

headline.main: Twitch Users Watch Billions of Hours of Video, but the Site Wants to Go Beyond Fortnite
headline.print_headline: Twitch Aims To Play More Than Games
